when in fields which have public access. </p>\n\n<p>Horses may be kept loose in fields crossed by PROWs, as long as they are not known to be dangerous.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You can be prosecuted if you keep a potentially dangerous animal on land crossed by a <abbr title=\"public right of way\">PROW</abbr>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Cross compliance</h2>\n<p>If a designated public right of way (<abbr title=\"public right of way\">PROW</abbr>) crosses your land and you claim agricultural payments under the Single Payments Scheme, make sure you’re familiar with <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://rpa.defra.gov.uk/rpa/index.nsf/UIMenu/814240C66F10CAC8802570C7004248D4?Opendocument\" title=\"Cross compliance\">cross compliance</a> rules. These rules apply to all your land - not just the land you claim for.</p>\n\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Coasts, countryside and creatures","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/citizenship%2Fcoasts-countryside.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes right of way, protecting landscapes and animal welfare","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=citizenship%2Fcoasts-countryside","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/citizenship/coasts-countryside"},"parent":{"title":"Citizenship and life in the UK","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/citizenship.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes voting and how government works","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=citizenship","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/citizenship"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/control-dog-public.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/control-dog-public","title":"Controlling your dog in public","format":"guide","updated_at":"2013-01-09T13:09:00+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/common-land-village-greens.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/common-land-vill